  "texts": [
    "Community structure is the tendency of networks to consist of groups of vertices where the density of edges within the group is much higher than the density of edges between groups.",
    "These groups of highly-connected vertices are called communities.",
    "There is no single formal accepted definition of a community or how dense the connections must be to form a community.",
    "Certainly a fully connected group of vertices, i.e., a clique, would constitute a community, but communities need not be so densely connected.",
    "We are interested in finding all of the communities of the network."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}